// Semantic direction:
// modelsjekking: Clarke, Emerson, Sifakis (Turing Award 2007) — automatically verify finite-state
//   systems against temporal logic specifications; returns counterexample if violated.
// LTL_logikk: linear-time temporal logic — properties of individual paths; AG(p→Fq) = "p always leads to q".
// CTL_logikk: computation tree logic — properties of branching time; EF(error) = "error is reachable".
// mu_kalkyle: subsumes CTL and LTL; μX.f(X) = least fixed point — most expressive modal mu-calculus.
// OBDD_representasjon: ordered BDDs canonically represent Boolean functions — symbolic state space.
// bounded_MC: unroll transitions k steps, encode as SAT — finds bugs in deep state spaces.
// CEGAR_algoritme: (1) abstract, (2) model check, (3) if spurious counterexample, refine — iterative.
// predicate_abstraction: keep only Boolean predicates over state — exponential reduction in state space.
// SMT_verifikasjon: satisfiability modulo theories — LIA, arrays, bitvectors for program verification.
// SLAM_verktøy: Microsoft's device driver verifier — found thousands of real Windows driver bugs.
// Kripke_struktur: (S, I, R, L) where S=states, I=initial, R=transitions, L=labelling with atoms.

// Primitive flow:
// spesifikasjon: AG(forespørsel → AF(svar))   (alltid: forespørsel leder til svar)
// modelsjekking: bygg Kripke-struktur M → sjekk M ⊨ φ → returner sant/moteksempel
// CEGAR: abstrakt(M) → sjekk → moteksempel → konkretiser → gjenta

